I know what I saw and I know
that you have to get this checked out.

134
00:06:46.364 --> 00:06:49.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
See this? Total shut down.
Didn't hear any of that.

135
00:06:49.367 --> 00:06:51.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[door opens]
-[Jacob] Frankie, you here?

136
00:06:51.285 --> 00:06:56.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Oh! Yes! But don't tell Grace.
-[door closes]

137
00:06:56.874 --> 00:06:58.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe you can talk some sense into her.

138
00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:00.294  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How you feeling?

139
00:07:01.420 --> 00:07:02.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Better now.

140
00:07:03.005 --> 00:07:05.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's get dinner. Ruby's?

141
00:07:05.508 --> 00:07:07.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I could really go for a mozzarella stick.

142
00:07:08.052 --> 00:07:09.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She needs to go to the hospital.

143
00:07:10.054 --> 00:07:11.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For a panic attack?

144
00:07:11.347 --> 00:07:13.057  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what she told you?

145
00:07:13.141 --> 00:07:16.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The EMT said it could have been
a neurological event.

146
00:07:16.394 --> 00:07:17.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

147
00:07:17.520 --> 00:07:20.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have neurological events all the time.

148
00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:24.068  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're called acid flashbacks
and they're the shit!

149
00:07:24.152 --> 00:07:26.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She looked really confused and out of it.

150
00:07:26.612 --> 00:07:28.948  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hello? Have you met me? That's my look!

151
00:07:29.031 --> 00:07:32.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Boom. Frankie burn. Hashtag roasted.

152
00:07:33.161 --> 00:07:35.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sounds like this isn't something
you mess around with.

153
00:07:35.705 --> 00:07:36.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, my God.

154
00:07:36.831 --> 00:07:40.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Would you Complaining Cathys
be happy if I made you a deal?

155
00:07:40.668 --> 00:07:44.088  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I will not go to the hospital,
but I will call my doctor.

156
00:07:44.172 --> 00:07:47.133  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And if he tells you
to go to the hospital, will you?

157
00:07:47.925 --> 00:07:50.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Yes.
-Deal. Call him. Now.

158
00:07:50.553 --> 00:07:51.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay.

159
00:07:54.015 --> 00:07:56.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[loud drone]

160
00:07:59.145 --> 00:08:01.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kidding. Give me your phone.

161
00:08:06.903 --> 00:08:07.737  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Peter.

162
00:08:08.404 --> 00:08:10.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Robert, you are on fire!

163
00:08:10.323 --> 00:08:12.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You are John Adams.
-Thank you.

164
00:08:12.116 --> 00:08:14.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look, do you know where my family is?

165
00:08:14.285 --> 00:08:17.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Okay. There is a slight situation,
but everything's fine now.

166
00:08:17.830 --> 00:08:21.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sol's on his way back and he'll tell you
all about it after the show.

167
00:08:21.459 --> 00:08:23.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What kind of situation?
With those protestors?

168
00:08:23.669 --> 00:08:27.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The buzz backstage is that Sol's ex
was taken to the hospital by ambulance.

169
00:08:27.798 --> 00:08:29.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Frankie? Oh, my God. What happened?

170
00:08:29.884 --> 00:08:33.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They don't know. But if you feel
compelled to go, which any person would,

171
00:08:33.179 --> 00:08:35.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
we would all completely understand.

172
00:08:36.015 --> 00:08:39.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know all your lines,
and your wig fits me... perfect.

173
00:08:39.143 --> 00:08:40.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You've been trying it on?
-It's my job to.

174
00:08:40.978 --> 00:08:43.898  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It is absolutely not, Steve.
-[man] Places please.

175
00:08:43.981 --> 00:08:48.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been texting with Sol and he says,
"Robert, be brave. The show must go on.

176
00:08:48.819 --> 00:08:50.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And it wouldn't hurt
if you paced it up a little."

177
00:08:50.821 --> 00:08:53.783  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-He said that last part?
-Damn it, Robert! There's no time!

178
00:08:53.866 --> 00:08:57.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"Frankie's home now and seems fine.
No need for Robert to worry."

179
00:08:58.037 --> 00:09:02.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, the only thing that gives me
pause is the use of the word "seems."

180
00:09:03.501 --> 00:09:04.627  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've got this.

181
00:09:04.710 --> 00:09:06.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shut the fuck up, Steve.

182
00:09:07.004 --> 00:09:08.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And sit the fuck down.

183
00:09:11.926 --> 00:09:13.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, thank God you're here, Dr...?

184
00:09:13.678 --> 00:09:14.762  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, just call me Mark.

185
00:09:14.845 --> 00:09:18.599  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mark. I must say, I'm impressed
anybody makes house calls these days.

186
00:09:18.683 --> 00:09:21.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, if someone needs me,
I will go anywhere.

187
00:09:21.894 --> 00:09:24.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I like to think of my patients
as my children.

188
00:09:24.480 --> 00:09:26.941  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, your daughter's being a real pill.

189
00:09:27.942 --> 00:09:29.902  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, that feels so good.

190
00:09:29.986 --> 00:09:30.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Frankie?

191
00:09:31.487 --> 00:09:32.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, Mark!

192
00:09:32.697 --> 00:09:36.117  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sorry to get you out here this late
for a brain glitch.

193
00:09:36.200 --> 00:09:39.287  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't worry about it.
I'll just do a quick examination.

194
00:09:39.370 --> 00:09:40.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's have a look at that tongue.

195
00:09:42.123 --> 00:09:44.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a little coated. Flaming Hot Funyuns?

196
00:09:44.917 --> 00:09:47.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughs] Right on the money, as per.

197
00:09:47.587 --> 00:09:50.798  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do you want us to clear out?
Give you some privacy?

198
00:09:50.881 --> 00:09:52.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, if you could back up just a bit.

199
00:09:53.718 --> 00:09:56.762  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I need to have a clear energy path
to bring in the shamanic spirits.

200
00:09:57.346 --> 00:09:58.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, God...

201
00:09:58.472 --> 00:10:04.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[moans, speaks ritualistic chants]

202
00:10:07.231 --> 00:10:09.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Allison knows we're waiting, right?

203
00:10:09.108 --> 00:10:11.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah. She just has to check out.
She'll be here in a minute.

204
00:10:11.402 --> 00:10:13.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are we gonna have to hear
about everything wrong with her?

205
00:10:13.613 --> 00:10:16.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't have time for
the "Ailments with Allison" show.

206
00:10:16.240 --> 00:10:17.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She fainted.

207
00:10:17.325 --> 00:10:19.619  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Because she always has to be
the center of attention,

208
00:10:19.702 --> 00:10:21.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
so she conjures up some kind of illness.

209
00:10:22.038 --> 00:10:25.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Bud, there's a name for it:
Fictitious Disorder.

210
00:10:25.625 --> 00:10:29.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
First of all, it's "Factitious Disorder"
and she doesn't have that. We checked.

211
00:10:29.086 --> 00:10:31.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-With a Factitian?
-That's not a thing.

212
00:10:31.339 --> 00:10:33.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Neither are her numerous diseases.

213
00:10:33.132 --> 00:10:35.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shut up, okay? Oh, here she comes.

214
00:10:37.845 --> 00:10:40.056  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, honey. What did the doctor say?

215
00:10:40.139 --> 00:10:41.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nothing.

216
00:10:41.515 --> 00:10:43.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's nothing. It's fine.

217
00:10:45.311 --> 00:10:46.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just... [sighs]

218
00:10:48.522 --> 00:10:52.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your chi is lower than I'd like it to be,
but these crystals should help.

219
00:10:54.612 --> 00:10:56.572  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd also like to do some Reiki.

220
00:10:56.656 --> 00:10:58.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, that would be great.

221
00:10:58.532 --> 00:11:01.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know what else would be great?
Getting a freaking MRI.

222
00:11:01.786 --> 00:11:04.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wow, you seem really angry.

223
00:11:04.789 --> 00:11:07.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-May I see your tongue?
-You may not.

224
00:11:07.166 --> 00:11:11.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, I don't think this
is helping Frankie.

225
00:11:11.087 --> 00:11:14.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I don't think this is a real thing.

226
00:11:14.298 --> 00:11:15.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't listen to her.

227
00:11:15.633 --> 00:11:18.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's some tea I'd like you
to take three times a day.

228
00:11:18.219 --> 00:11:19.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Frankie] Hmm.

229
00:11:19.512 --> 00:11:22.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know what?
If you could brew it, it would be great.

230
00:11:23.683 --> 00:11:24.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tea?

231
00:11:24.642 --> 00:11:26.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Tea.
-Tea.

232
00:11:28.896 --> 00:11:32.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Marshmallow root, dandelion leaf,
reishi mushroom, wild lettuce,

233
00:11:32.608 --> 00:11:35.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and a little something
I like to call "Mark Bark."

234
00:11:35.236 --> 00:11:38.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, let me get my wizard staff
and pointed hat.

235
00:11:38.197 --> 00:11:39.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That is a different tea.

236
00:11:39.281 --> 00:11:41.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on, Grace. Who's the doctor here?

237
00:11:41.826 --> 00:11:43.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nobody!

238
00:11:43.160 --> 00:11:45.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nobody's the doctor here!

239
00:11:50.501 --> 00:11:52.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wow. [groans]

240
00:11:52.294 --> 00:11:54.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's like nothing
I've ever smelled before

241
00:11:54.713 --> 00:11:56.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and I work with fertilizer.

242
00:11:56.382 --> 00:11:58.134  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is ridiculous.

243
00:11:58.217 --> 00:12:00.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look, I know this isn't your thing,

244
00:12:00.344 --> 00:12:03.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and it might not even be my thing,
but it is her thing.

245
00:12:03.514 --> 00:12:07.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, her thing is also holding her breath
every time a plane flies overhead.

246
00:12:07.309 --> 00:12:11.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Say what you want, but a plane's never
emptied its toilets over your house.

247
00:12:11.689 --> 00:12:13.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's why she does that?

248
00:12:13.357 --> 00:12:14.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah.

249
00:12:14.608 --> 00:12:17.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Mark] Hey guys,
be sure to keep the tea covered!

250
00:12:17.570 --> 00:12:20.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's a lot of
star-constellation energy in there!

251
00:12:20.906 --> 00:12:24.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Makes total fucking sense! Thanks, Mark!

252
00:12:24.952 --> 00:12:27.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Mark chanting indistinctly]

253
00:12:30.875 --> 00:12:32.084  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here it is.

254
00:12:32.168 --> 00:12:34.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, great. Thanks, you guys.

255
00:12:34.378 --> 00:12:36.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, remember...

256
00:12:36.130 --> 00:12:40.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you are a student of the leaf
and the tea is your plant teacher.

257
00:12:41.093 --> 00:12:42.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just drink mindfully.

258
00:12:42.553 --> 00:12:44.930  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And try not to throw it up
because it tastes like horse shit.

259
00:12:45.014 --> 00:12:48.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You might want to hold your nose.
The smell alone could kill you.

260
00:12:50.227 --> 00:12:51.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm.

261
00:12:52.104 --> 00:12:53.063  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's not bad.

262
00:12:54.440 --> 00:12:56.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It doesn't really have any taste at all.

263
00:12:56.400 --> 00:12:58.652  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let me make sure you made it right.

264
00:12:59.028 --> 00:13:01.030  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[sputters]
-[Grace] Oh.

265
00:13:01.113 --> 00:13:03.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, that's right. [exhales]

266
00:13:12.708 --> 00:13:15.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Anything?
-Nothing!

267
00:13:15.252 --> 00:13:16.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why can't I taste anything?

268
00:13:17.046 --> 00:13:19.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know, but you should probably
get to the hospital.

269
00:13:19.798 --> 00:13:21.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-No!
-Oh!

270
00:13:21.550 --> 00:13:22.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Frankie, we had a deal.

271
00:13:22.927 --> 00:13:26.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, but I didn't think this would happen!
[smacking]

272
