Well, I mean...

413
00:20:13.253 --> 00:20:15.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-This is very...
-Surprising.

414
00:20:15.464 --> 00:20:17.007  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Surprising. Yes.

415
00:20:17.090 --> 00:20:20.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But it's also... challenging?

416
00:20:20.510 --> 00:20:22.262  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Very, very challenging.

417
00:20:23.055 --> 00:20:24.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But also...

418
00:20:24.723 --> 00:20:26.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Information that is...
-Private.

419
00:20:27.059 --> 00:20:29.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes. But also--

420
00:20:30.062 --> 00:20:31.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
For fuck's sake, Bud,
just tell me what you think.

421
00:20:34.399 --> 00:20:35.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think...

422
00:20:40.822 --> 00:20:41.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Me, too.

423
00:20:46.578 --> 00:20:49.373  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens, slams shut]

424
00:20:54.836 --> 00:20:56.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You ruined my opening night.

425
00:20:57.005 --> 00:20:58.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

426
00:20:58.840 --> 00:21:00.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Frankie got sick and I--

427
00:21:00.425 --> 00:21:04.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not talking about you walking out
on my show twice.

428
00:21:04.429 --> 00:21:09.393  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And while that was extremely annoying,
I'm talking about that wretched heckler.

429
00:21:09.476 --> 00:21:12.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Oh, that was unbelievable.
-Yes!

430
00:21:12.312 --> 00:21:16.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I guess something must have gotten him
really revved up.

431
00:21:16.441 --> 00:21:19.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I... Robert--

432
00:21:19.695 --> 00:21:21.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know it was you, Sol.

433
00:21:21.738 --> 00:21:23.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You threw the Pepsi at that kid,
didn't you?

434
00:21:23.991 --> 00:21:26.576  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It was a Mr. Bubbly
and it was an accident.

435
00:21:26.660 --> 00:21:30.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, you accidentally
accelerated that situation.

436
00:21:30.914 --> 00:21:33.917  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you had just let them be,
like I asked you to,

437
00:21:34.001 --> 00:21:35.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
no one would have paid any attention

438
00:21:35.669 --> 00:21:38.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and they would have just crawled back
under the rock they came from.

439
00:21:39.047 --> 00:21:40.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But if I hadn't said anything--

440
00:21:40.340 --> 00:21:43.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'd be celebrating over drinks
at the cast party.

441
00:21:43.135 --> 00:21:44.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What was I supposed to do?

442
00:21:44.594 --> 00:21:46.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let. It. Go.

443
00:21:47.055 --> 00:21:49.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No! I can't.

444
00:21:49.349 --> 00:21:53.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"The only thing necessary for the triumph
of evil is for good men to do nothing."

445
00:21:53.854 --> 00:21:57.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My father had that quote framed
and hung in our living room.

446
00:21:57.941 --> 00:21:59.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I saw it every day.

447
00:22:02.070 --> 00:22:04.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not going to let this go, Robert.

448
00:22:04.781 --> 00:22:09.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Especially... Especially after what
they did to you today.

449
00:22:11.705 --> 00:22:17.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Those people...
fucked with the wrong bored old man!

450
00:22:19.504 --> 00:22:24.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, go in there
and wash that makeup off your face.

451
00:22:32.893 --> 00:22:35.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I planted these crab apple trees
when I bought the place.

452
00:22:35.687 --> 00:22:39.024  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's a family of mule deer
who come by every evening.

453
00:22:39.107 --> 00:22:41.902  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's a mother, and father,
two little ones.

454
00:22:41.985 --> 00:22:45.197  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They've just about picked this tree clean.

455
00:22:45.280 --> 00:22:47.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, it sounds so beautiful.

456
00:22:48.658 --> 00:22:51.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Yeah, they do get gassy.
-[door opens]

457
00:22:51.870 --> 00:22:52.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Grace] Knock-knock.

458
00:22:53.038 --> 00:22:56.458  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You left your reading glasses downstairs.
I thought you might need them.

459
00:22:56.541 --> 00:22:57.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

460
00:22:57.834 --> 00:23:01.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And, um, you left these downstairs, too.

461
00:23:01.505 --> 00:23:04.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Since you have your glasses,
maybe you want to take a look.

462
00:23:04.341 --> 00:23:06.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If it's all right with you,
I'll read them later.

463
00:23:07.552 --> 00:23:10.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Have you taken your blood pressure yet?
-No.

464
00:23:10.472 --> 00:23:13.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Would you like me to show you how--
-No. I would not.

465
00:23:16.186 --> 00:23:17.479  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay.

466
00:23:19.439 --> 00:23:23.443  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, by the way, if you're still
thinking about going to Santa Fe,

467
00:23:23.527 --> 00:23:26.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it is really not a good idea
to fly right now.

468
00:23:26.571 --> 00:23:29.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're thinking maybe we'd drive.
Make it a nice road trip.

469
00:23:30.075 --> 00:23:31.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, I asked about that, too.

470
00:23:31.827 --> 00:23:34.371  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She's not supposed to sit
for long stretches.

471
00:23:34.454 --> 00:23:37.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, she has to get up
and walk around every half hour.

472
00:23:37.457 --> 00:23:39.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For circulation.

473
00:23:39.376 --> 00:23:40.752  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who did you ask?

474
00:23:41.711 --> 00:23:42.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dr. Weintraub.

475
00:23:42.921 --> 00:23:44.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You called him?
-Yes!

476
00:23:44.923 --> 00:23:47.425  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To find out if it was all right
for you to travel so soon.

477
00:23:47.509 --> 00:23:49.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You called my doctor?

478
00:23:49.302 --> 00:23:50.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Frankie. It's okay.

479
00:23:51.054 --> 00:23:53.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, it's not okay.

480
00:23:53.265 --> 00:23:55.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't get to call my doctor.

481
00:23:55.475 --> 00:23:57.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're not my mother.

482
00:23:57.185 --> 00:23:59.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're not my husband.

483
00:23:59.229 --> 00:24:03.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
From now on, if I have any questions,
I'll call him.

484
00:24:03.275 --> 00:24:04.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, will you?

485
00:24:04.442 --> 00:24:07.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Because you were going to take a trip
without ever talking to him.

486
00:24:09.281 --> 00:24:10.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where are you going? Don't leave.

487
00:24:11.074 --> 00:24:13.785  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not leaving.

488
00:24:13.869 --> 00:24:17.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I just think you two need for me
not to be here.

489
00:24:18.290 --> 00:24:20.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[Frankie sighs]
-[door opens]

490
00:24:21.293 --> 00:24:23.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why are you angry with me?

491
00:24:23.461 --> 00:24:25.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Would you prefer if I gave you a kiss
and said thank you?

492
00:24:25.964 --> 00:24:28.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes! I was right!

493
00:24:29.009 --> 00:24:32.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There is something serious
that you needed to know about

494
00:24:32.304 --> 00:24:33.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
so you could take care of it.

495
00:24:34.389 --> 00:24:37.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is not what I want my life
to look like!

496
00:24:37.392 --> 00:24:40.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So you have to take a few pills
and check your blood pressure.

497
00:24:40.854 --> 00:24:42.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's not your life.

498
00:24:42.189 --> 00:24:43.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I take pills.

499
00:24:43.899 --> 00:24:46.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My God, this is America,
everybody takes pills.

500
00:24:46.860 --> 00:24:48.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's not just the pills.

501
00:24:48.737 --> 00:24:51.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was much happier not knowing.

502
00:24:51.781 --> 00:24:56.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now I'm going to wake up every morning
thinking about spots on my brain.

503
00:24:56.161 --> 00:24:58.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Every time I stumble over a word
I'm going to think,

504
00:24:59.039 --> 00:25:00.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"It's happening again!"

505
00:25:00.957 --> 00:25:05.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Or wonder "Will I even get
to finish my sentence?"

506
00:25:05.962 --> 00:25:08.006  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It scares the shit out of me.

507
00:25:08.089 --> 00:25:11.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, you want to talk about scared?
Let's talk about it.

508
00:25:12.260 --> 00:25:13.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Today, in the car?

509
00:25:13.762 --> 00:25:17.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought I was watching you die
right in front of me.

510
00:25:17.724 --> 00:25:20.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was terrified that
I was losing my best friend.

511
00:25:20.936 --> 00:25:24.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I did what I was supposed to do
for somebody that I care about.

512
00:25:25.023 --> 00:25:29.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I did the right thing
and I am not gonna apologize for it.

513
00:25:37.202 --> 00:25:40.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Would you please tell Jacob to come in
on your way out?

514
00:25:42.332 --> 00:25:44.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Bahamas' "Lost In The Light" playing]

515
00:25:50.298 --> 00:25:51.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door closes]

516
00:25:52.968 --> 00:25:53.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

517
00:25:55.720 --> 00:25:57.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I'm lost in the light ♪</i>

518
00:25:58.765 --> 00:26:00.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I pray for the night ♪</i>

519
00:26:01.977 --> 00:26:05.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>♪ To take me</i>
<i>To take me too ♪</i>

520
00:26:08.108 --> 00:26:10.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ After so many words ♪</i>

521
00:26:11.111 --> 00:26:13.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Still nothing's heard ♪</i>

522
00:26:14.239 --> 00:26:17.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Don't know what we should do ♪</i>

523
00:26:19.369 --> 00:26:23.415  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>♪ So if someone could see me now</i>
<i>Let them see you ♪</i>

524
00:26:23.498 --> 00:26:28.128  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chorus humming]

525
00:26:49.733 --> 00:26:51.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman] <i>Okay, good night.</i>

